De_Strife is a medium to large sized map that takes place in a group of storage warehouses. I started this map while I was working on other projects for the mod Off-Limits. My goal was to make a very balanced map and I think I accompished that pretty well after lots of playtesting in my computer class at school. It is a Defuse map that supports 32 players.

After 6 months of hard work, the map's finally finished.  I'd like to thank FreakyMe for rewriting the map story description, Kyle for running testing servers for me, and Jake for helping me out with making a few things.

UPDATE:  I BSP zipped in the models and materials due to popular demand, it still has a res for the radar overview.



De_stratocorp is set in an abandoned laboratory created by a company named StratoCorp.

StratoCorp was shut down when the government discovered the dangerous nature of their experiments, and the lab has long since fallen into disuse. It's 5 years later and a terrorist group, using the lab as a base of operations, has discovered a pathogen in the making; capable of wiping out an entire country in the event of open viral warfare. The terrorists plan to detonate explosives near one of the containment chambers, and cause the release of the virus inside. The US government has caught wind of this plan and has sent an elite Counter-Terrorism group to stop the operation..

Fast paced, action packed source map carefully designed to separate the men from the boys. Blind shooting and selfish tactics will get you no where on this map.

I have deliberately kept it relatively simple and have carefully placed every prop to maximize the need to stick with your team. Is is a pretty small map but has 3 floors and has been designed to cover all fighting styles.

IF YOU CAN DOMINATE THIS MAP... YOU CAN DOMINATE ANY MAP!!!!

More info on this and the bonus map included in this pack in the read me file. Don't forget to read during install.

<3 <3

This is the final of strata, a mid-sized defusal map with an industrial theme (imaginative eh? ) Layout is fairly straight forward with 3 or 4 interconnecting routes and quite a closed design, rather than large and open (think more prodigy/nuke than port/compound). Its mostly a bright, sunny map with only a couple of darkspots in the interior sections.
Lots of rooms and 3 important building. All in the night

De_stock conveys a warm, maritime atmosphere, inviting you to extend your summer holidays by having a swim in the deep blue sea. Terrorists start from behind the factory, which is served by train, while CT spawn is located throughout the quay. There are 4 to 6 different paths to get from one end of the map to the other.
Very different from de_port, de_stock has pleasant graphics and a worth-seeing structure. Much attention has been paid to the sound environment with the addition of 6 hi-fi wav sounds not contained in the gcf.

de_stella

Terrorist: Seeking revenge on your old high school teachers, you seize Stella Maris Academy and decide to bomb the building. You either must plant the explosives downstairs, in the library (Bombsite A) or plant it at the end of the upstairs hallway (Bombsite B). Beware, the police have already arrived!

Counter-Terrorist: After receiving a report that terrorists have sized Stella Maris Academy, you move into the building. You must prevent the terrorist from bombing the school. Act with extreme prejudice.


by Gonzell
Special Thanks to:
Shankus and others (obtaining blueprints)

Play testers:
Newfie, Destro, Zaralus, Shankus, Scerge, Solid Snake, Finlay12, King Mikey, Violator and others

More Information:
This is actually a map of my old high school. Its not the entire school mainly because of performance reasons (its just too big). If you are wondering if my school really does have tables flipped over in the hallways and bombsite markings the answer is: You're an idiot. Thanks for playing and happy fragging!

Note: This map is still under construction. Although, this version is perfectly playable and is nearing the final release.

Terrorists have an underground facility with secret plans, the counter-terrorists came across on it and entered from the opened SILO 2, which is in preparation for taking off. But Terrorists don't want their plans to be discovered and decided to self-destruct the whole base. This can be done if the rocket in the silo is bombed or the biological weapons in the train loading station. This corresponds to bombsite A and B.

This map is a Cylinder like station (On the outside) that is being attacked by some raiders (Terrorist) that are trying to invade. It's dark, gloomy and with a lot of secret passages this map has some good techniques. Either the CT's can approach the tunnels with full force, or re-arrange themselves in a good defensive situation. While the terrorists can either go full-on force through the tunnels, or take sneaky passages under the station to get to places within cover. Up to you to decide.

This map does have some simple rooms; but this is an old map that I just simply never published. I will most likely do an improved version within months time or so. But for now I hope you enjoy this game =)

I've timed the walk distance to each team; and they both clash at the tunnels!

Hope you enjoy! :) 

-- I love feedback and opinions!

De_Station17_underground_beta

This is a beta version of my map so it still has to be tweaked a bit more before the final release.

Background:
Before the combine oppression of City17, all was not well, there was still great stife and civil unrest. One extremist political group had been ignored far too long, in a series of attacks they would bring the city to its knees; the world would hear their demands.
The Terrorists have already begun their attack, derailing a train and blowing a hole in the underground platform giving them direct access to the server room.

Terrorist:
Secure and bomb either the train carrage (A) or the server room (B) to cease all train transport in the city.
You may need to eliminate the CT team so you can later succeed at your objective.

Counter-Terrorists:
Terrorist have stormed the ticket office, killing several civilans, eliminate the threat and stop the bombing at all costs.

Original Half-life 2 station by valve
All additions and modifications are by Ben Andrews.
Any feedback e-mail Benlandrews@aol.com

NOTE: I did not create, or in anyway participate, in the creation of this map. I solely submit it for others to enjoy. Thanks to RuudVanPistolrooy for giving me permission to submit it. AUTHOR'S NOTES: So here's the latest WIP version of the map. I wasn't sure if I wanted to release this version of it, since it's still needing a serious last layer of polish and fixing up. However I think the map needs a last round of feedback before I go for a final. Known issues: - Some texture alignment bugs. - Model collisions. - Some of the models need re-skinning (remaking possibly, I pretty much suck at modelling still). - Totally unoptimised - FPS is shite in places. - Nav mesh is rough and dirty with no place painting. - You can escape from the map in some places. - Some z-fighting where the tree shadow overlays hit displacements. - Soundscapes appear broken in this build. - Some of the overlays are a bit crap. - Terrorists have more spawnpoints than CT All comments and crits appreciated. I am pretty much set on the layout now, I just want to concentrate on making it look nicer and fixing bugs. http://www.fragnbag.com EXTRA NOTES: - The spawnpoints seem a bit messed up. Terrors have 13 as far as I coult tell, while Counter-Terrors only have 10. Still, the map is very playable. - Check out the previous version of this map here: Click - I included a bzipped2 version in the .rar, for easy use with fast download servers.
